- verification of an imposed radiative heat flux boundary condition

- P1 approximation as a radiation model

- polydisperse random particle packing placed between two isothermal black
  plates

- pseudo-scattering used for removal of heat flux oscillations

- temperature profile tested against an analytical solution
  (Heaslet and Warming, Int. J. Heat Mass Transfer, 1965)

- more details in Macak, Goniva, Radl "Predictions of the P1 approximation for
  radiative heat transfer in heterogeneous granular media" (2022)
